A brief history of specifications is given below.  Websites are given where the
official specification lives, but they have all been copied into this directory
for convenience.  Note that some of these links may be broken.

RFCs (http://www.irchelp.org/irchelp/rfc/):
  RFC 1459 (original RFC; superseded by RFC 2810 -- RFC 2813)
    http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1459
  RFC 2810 (IRC architecture)
    http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2810
  RFC 2811 (IRC channel management)
    http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2811
    This mostly applies only to servers
  RFC 2812 (IRC client protocol)
    http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2812
  RFC 2813 (IRC server protocol)
    http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2813
    This applies only to servers

File Transfer / CTCP extensions:
  DCC specification (superseded fully by CTCP specification)
    http://www.irchelp.org/irchelp/rfc/dccspec.html
  CTCP specification
    http://www.irchelp.org/irchelp/rfc/ctcpspec.html
  Updated CTCP specification
    http://www.invlogic.com/irc/ctcp.html
    This is not fully supported by clients
  Turbo DCC
    http://www.visualirc.net/tech-tdcc.php
  RDCC / DCC REVERSE / DCC RSEND / Reverse/Firewall DCC / FSERVs
  XDCC (eXtended DCC)
  CTCP/2
    http://www.invlogic.com/irc/ctcp2_intro.html
  SDCC / DCC SCHAT (Secure DCC)
  See http://www.kvirc.de/docu/doc_dcc_connection.html for an overall comparison
  and explanation of the extensions to DCC.

  DCC2 (superseds DCC, CTCP, updated CTCP, CTCP/2) -- http://www.dcc2.org/
    http://www.ietf.org/proceedings/61/IDs/draft-smith-irc-dcc2-negotiation-00.txt
    http://www.dcc2.org/files/dcc2/draft-smith-irc-dcc2-files-00.txt
    http://www.dcc2.org/files/dcc2/draft-smith-irc-dcc2-negotiation-00.txt
    This doesn't seem done

Extension Support:
  ISupport
    http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-brocklesby-irc-isupport-03
    Response code 005; supported by most servers
  Updated ISupport
    http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-hardy-irc-isupport-00
  IRC Capabilities
    http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-mitchell-irc-capabilities-01
    http://www.leeh.co.uk/draft-mitchell-irc-capabilities-02.html
    Standardization for reporting extensions

Authentication:
  SASL authentication (PLAIN and BLOWFISH)
    http://hg.atheme.org/atheme/atheme/raw-file/tip/doc/SASL
    Depends on IRC Capabilities
  NickServ
  Auth?

Other:
  DCC Whiteboard Specification
    http://www.visualirc.net/tech-wboard.php
  IRCX (extends RFC 1459)
    http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-pfenning-irc-extensions-04
    Microsoft's extension to IRC

URL Scheme:
  irc:
    http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-mirashi-url-irc-01
  irc: and ircs:
    http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-butcher-irc-url-04
